'''Otis Frampton''' is a comic book writer and illustrator who has contributed 406 sketch cards to the [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']] trading card collection and created content for [[StarWars.com]], including two Star Wars Kids: Learn To Draw tutorials ([[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] and [[Salacious B. Crumb/Legends|Salacious Crumb]]) and an Emperor [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] Halloween mask.

He is also an artist on the YouTube series ''[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCHCph-_jLba_9atyCZJPLQQ How It Should Have Ended]'' and has worked on several of the ''Star Wars'' parodies that the series has produced.

After pitching a potential comic book series called ''Star Wars: Jawa Adventures'' for several months, he was contacted by [[IDW Publishing]] to create a variant cover for the [[Star Wars Adventures (2017) 8|eighth issue]] of their [[Star Wars Adventures (2017)|''Star Wars Adventures'']] comic book series featuring his [[Jawa]]s,<ref name="Variant">{{Twitter|otisframpton|status/931256861663399936|Otis Frampton|quote=#ThrowbackThursday to me inking my #StarWarsAdventutes variant cover in @Procreate. #utinni #g♥nk|archivedate=20200814124120}}</ref> but also a 7-page ''Tales from Wild Space'' back-up comic for the issue.<ref name="7pages">{{Twitter|otisframpton|status/926536219726635008|Otis Frampton|quote=Yep! I'm doing a 7 page backup story in Star Wars Adventures and a variant cover for the issue.|archivedate=20200814124119}}</ref>

